2026-06-06
- Restructured the project so the repository root contains `backend/` and `frontend/`.
- Moved the SQLite explorer frontend back to the top-level `frontend/` folder.
- Updated backend runtime paths, docs, and Railway watch patterns to match the new layout.
- Moved the example environment file to the repository root and updated dotenv loading to read from root `.env`.
- Fixed the local reload helper so it enters `backend/` before launching uvicorn from the root project.
- Added a legacy Railway config shim at `apps/backend/railway.toml` so deployments still pointing at the old service config path can initialize successfully while the canonical config remains in `backend/railway.toml`.
- Added root-level Railway bridge files (`requirements.txt` and `start.sh`) so Railpack can detect Python from the repository root and start the backend through the new root layout.
- Updated Railway start commands to call `bash start.sh` instead of depending on a backend-local entrypoint.
- Expanded Railway watch patterns to include the root deployment bridge files so changes to `requirements.txt` and `start.sh` trigger rebuilds too.
- Added a root-level `railway.toml` and updated deploy docs so Railway can target the repository root cleanly with the new layout.
- Changed root `requirements.txt` to list backend dependencies directly because Railpack installs it before nested project files such as `backend/requirements.txt` are available in the build layer.
- Made SQLite explorer source parsing accept a single JSON object as well as an array, and documented Railway SQLite paths using `/app/data/chat.sqlite3`.
